sub_title: Technician - Protein expression and purification, at Hubrecht Institute
summary:
I am a M.Sc. graduate who recently moved to the netherlands in search of exciting career opportunities within life science.
Guided by curiosity and interest for science, I have been adventurous during my education and studied in various scientific envronments. This has given me a wide range of competences including organic chemistry, behavioural and molecular biology.

I have experience with:
Assay development of spectrophotometric luminescence assays, 
Design, expression and purification (FPLC, IMAC/SEC) of recombinant proteins in E.Coli.
PCR, Electrophoresis (DNA, SDS-PAGE)
Invertebrate model organism (Drosophila melanogaster).
Python programming.

As a colleague, I am passionate, patient and enthusiastic both socially and in my work, I have a strong analytical mind and I love problem solving. I possess excellent communication skills obtained through presentations and discussions, throughout projects and various courses during my education.

Feel free to contact me at Andersdid@live.dk.
